Directions:
\xe2\x80\xa2	Take 2 Oreo cookies.

b'Make these easy #Halloween ghost and monster treats:ghost:with kids from @christy_l_kitchen! Pick up cookie cutters, marshmallows, white chocolate and @KelloggsRiceKrispies cereal at Rite Aid! Check out our Stories to see how she does it and click the link in our bio for store locations. Directions below:

1. Melt #marshmallows and 2 tbsp butter in a pot to a a glue-like consistency
2. Slowly add a half a bag of Rice Krispies and mix it in altogether
3. Use a cookie cutter to help mold the mixture into the shape; immediately take it out of the mold and let it cool and set completely
4. Melt white and green chocolate separately and apply it on the Rice Krispie treat; let it harden. (You can also make your frosting using corn starch and sugar and then add natural food coloring or extracted vegetable juice to it.)
5.  Use white icing for the monster eyes and a bakery decorative gel to make the pupils and monster features
6. Add in mini sticks to create a marshmallow krispie pop'

b'Treat your kids to some #slime-tastic #Halloween fun at home with this simple @Starburst #DIY #recipe from our friend @its_mar_y_sol. Shop in-store for ingredients or tap here or the link in our bio for #Starburst, and get the recipe: :jack-o-lantern:
 
Ingredients:
 
1 bag (14 oz) Starburst
1/4 cup cornstarch
1/4 cup icing sugar
 
Instructions:
 
1.  Separate Starburst by color; place each in heatproof bowl. Place bowls of Starburst over saucepan of simmering water until melted.
 
2.  Whisk cornstarch with icing sugar; dust over work surface. Carefully turn out melted Starburst over top. Mixture will be hot; let cool for 5 minutes. 
 
3.  Knead melted Starburst with cornstarch mixture, pull and stretch to work air into the slime.
 
4.  Go slime crazy! Nibble or play \xe2\x80\x98til your hearts content'

b'With so many #sunscreen options available, how do you choose the right one? @the.local.pharmacist breaks it down here: 
.
Find one with broad-spectrum coverage (UVA & UVB protection), is easy to apply and feels good on YOUR skin:thumbs_up:! 
.
There are 2 types of sunscreens, Physical and Chemical.
.
Physical, or mineral, sunscreens include ingredients zinc oxide and titanium dioxide. They block and scatter UV radiation before it can penetrate the skin. They sit on top of the skin and start protecting immediately. Although they can be a little more difficult to apply and may leave a white residue, they\xe2\x80\x99re less irritating and a good option for those with sensitive skin. The FDA has declared that these sunscreen ingredients are \xe2\x80\x9cgenerally regarded as safe and effective.\xe2\x80\x9d
 
Chemical sunscreens work by absorbing UV rays, changing them to heat, then releasing the heat from the skin:hot_springs_selector:. The most common ingredients include oxybenzone, avobenzone, homosalate, octisalate, octinoxate, and octocrylene. Because absorption into the skin is required for effective protection, these sunscreens should be applied 30 minutes before going outdoors. When compared to physical sunscreens, these are lightweight, invisible and easier to apply, but may cause allergic reactions and irritate sensitive skin.
 
You can find sunscreen formulations as creams, gels, lotions, oils, sprays, sticks, or pastes. Gels might be easier for hairy areas, sprays for wet skin:sweat_droplets:, creams for dry skin and faces, and sticks for around the eyes:eyes:. Do not use sprays near your face and be careful not to inhale.
 
Always use a broad spectrum sunscreen with an SPF of 30+ every day, even when it\xe2\x80\x99s cloudy. (The higher the SPF #, the longer time it protects.) The average adult should use about 1 ounce:lotion_bottle:(2 tablespoons) for full application. REAPPLY every 2 hours and immediately after swimming :woman_swimming_selector: or excessive sweating.
.
You can also protect yourself by limiting :sun_selector: exposure during peak hours from 10am to 4pm, seeking shade when possible :beach_with_umbrella: and wearing protective clothing, a hat :billed_cap: and UV-blocking sunglasses :sunglasses:.
.
Sources: American Academy of Pediatrics, American Academy of Dermatology, Skin Cancer Foundation, Mayo Clinic'

b":fire:Beat the Heat! - How to Recognize and Prevent Heat-Related Illness
.
A beautiful #Summer day is a time to enjoy the outdoors, but unprotected and/or prolonged exposure to the sun:sun_selector: can be dangerous. Here are steps we can take to prepare ourselves to enjoy the summer (@the.local.pharmacist):
.
:hot_face:Heat-related illnesses are comprised of 3 conditions -- heat cramps, heat exhaustion, and heat stroke. Heat cramps are the cramping of major muscles:flexed_biceps_light_skin_tone:(quads, hamstrings, core, arms), that are stressed in a hot environment. If other symptoms are included, such as light-headedness, weakness, nausea, vomiting, or headache, we move to heat exhaustion. The most critical and severe condition is heat stroke. Heat stroke is identified by a very high fever:thermometer: (103\xc2\xbaF and up), :pouting_face:hot, red skin without signs of sweating, a rapid pulse and :exploding_head:throbbing headache. :ambulance: Seek emergency medical help immediately if heat stroke is suspected!
.
People most at risk of heat-related illnesses are seniors, children, athletes and outdoor workers. Try to prevent illness by drinking plenty of fluids, staying away from alcohol and caffeine, wearing light clothing, and if possible, limiting outdoor activity during peak temperature times (mid-day). If you can't limit it, consider using a balanced electrolyte drink along with water, and try to rest in cool, shaded areas whenever possible.:umbrella_on_ground: :deciduous_tree: 
.
If you are in a situation where you are taking care of someone who may be suffering from heat stroke, immediately call :hospital:911, move the person to a cool place, loosen clothing to help air circulate over the body, and spray or sponge :sweat_droplets:cool water onto the body until emergency help arrives.
.
Source: @cdcgov @mayoclinic"

b'From :hamburger:meats to :ear_of_corn:veggies, outdoor grilling is a great way to enjoy food with family, especially on July 4th :collision:, the most popular barbecuing holiday. However, every year, an estimated 1 in 6 Americans get sick from foodborne diseases. Remember to follow these FOOD SAFETY tips from @the.local.pharmacist to help prevent food poisoning:
.
CLEAN-SEPARATE-COOK-CHILL 
* :soap:Clean - Wash hands and work surfaces before, during and after preparing food
* :left-right_arrow_selector:Separate - Separate raw meats from ready to eat foods. Also use separate cutting boards
* :cooking:Cook - Cook food to the right internal temperature to kill harmful bacteria. Use a food thermometer :thermometer_selector: to ensure foods are cooked to these safe internal temperatures: 
\xe2\x80\xa2	145\xc2\xb0F for whole cuts of beef, pork, veal, lamb (+ allow meat to rest for 3 min. before carving or eating)
\xe2\x80\xa2	160\xc2\xb0F for ground meats, such as beef and pork
\xe2\x80\xa2	165\xc2\xb0F for all poultry, including ground chicken and turkey
\xe2\x80\xa2	165\xc2\xb0F for leftovers and casseroles
\xe2\x80\xa2	145\xc2\xb0F for fresh ham (raw)
\xe2\x80\xa2	145\xc2\xb0F for fin fish, or cook until flesh is opaque
* :ice:Chill - Keep your refrigerator at 40\xc2\xbaF or below. Refrigerate leftovers within 2 hrs of cooking or within 1 hr if food is exposed to temps 90\xc2\xbaF or above.
.
IF YOU THINK YOU HAVE FOOD POISONING
:nauseated_face:Symptoms of food poisoning include upset stomach, stomach cramps, nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, and fever. It may take hours or days before developing symptoms. Make sure to drink plenty of fluids to prevent dehydration if suffering from food poisoning.
.
:woman_health_worker_selector: See a healthcare provider for more severe symptoms, including bloody stools, :thermometer:fever of 102\xc2\xbaF or higher, frequent vomiting that prevents keeping liquids down (which can lead to dehydration), or diarrhea lasting more than 3 days.
.
Source: @cdcgov and foodsafety.gov'

b'"Leaves of Three, Let it Be!":herb:This famous phrase refers to poison ivy and poison oak plants with three leaflets coming from a central stem. Poison sumac, a similar plant, typically has 7\xe2\x80\x9313 leaflets arranged in pairs with a single leaflet at the end. :question_mark:But, did you know, the leaves of these plants change colors throughout the year. Starting as red-tinged green leaves in the spring, they advance to deep green to eventually fall colors, yellow, gold, red. All 3 plants contain an oily resin, called urushiol, which causes allergic contact dermatitis. :pine_decoration: Urushiol is an invisible, oily, clear substance that oozes from crushed or cut poison ivy leaves and spreads very easily. :magnifying_glass_tilted_left:At first, the rash is red, itchy, and may have swelling. The reaction can increase and lead to intense itching, inflammation, and papules. Read on for treatment tips: :bathtub: Oatmeal baths and cool compresses may be used to help relieve some symptoms. Over-the-counter (OTC) topical steroid cream (i.e., hydrocortisone) may also help with the itching and inflammation when treating mild to moderate symptoms. Hydrocortisone may be used on all body areas except around the eyes and eyelids and should not be used for longer than 7 days. OTC drying agents (e.g. calamine, aluminum acetate, zinc oxide, witch hazel, zinc acetate, sodium bicarbonate) may help minimize the oozing of fluid from blisters. :hospital:Consult your physician if the rash is on your face, eyes or genitals or if it covers a large portion of your body. Also, seek medical attention for children under 2 years of age, there are signs of infection, or your symptoms do not improve after 7 days.

Sources: @the.local.pharmacist
https://www.fda.gov/forConsumers/ConsumerUpdates/ucm049342.htm
https://www.cdc.gov/niosh/topics/plants/'

b'Bug bites be gone. Some tips this season from @the.local.pharmacist in Wolcott, CT: :mosquito:Insect repellents are an effective way to protect ourselves from mosquitoes, ticks, and other insects, along with the illnesses they may transmit, like Lyme Disease, Eastern Equine Encephalitis Virus, West Nile Virus, and Zika Virus. :thinking_face:Look for a product that contains one of the following ingredients:
:black_small_square_selector:DEET (Typically found in OFF! products)
:black_small_square_selector:Picaridin (Found in Natrapel Insect Repellent Spray)
:black_small_square_selector:Oil of Lemon Eucalyptus :lemon: (Found in Cutter Lemon Eucalyptus) and other non-DEET products like @BabyGanics Natural Insect Repellent Wipes.:thumbs_up_light_skin_tone: Choose a product based on the type of outdoor activity you\xe2\x80\x99ll be participating in and the amount of time you need it to work. Sweat resistant products may be a good choice for higher intensity outdoor activities. The length of protection depends on the concentration of the active ingredient. Higher concentrations do not work better, but they do work longer! :stopwatch:For example, a spray containing 5% DEET, will provide almost 1.5 hours of protection, whereas a 25% DEET product provides about 5 hours of protection. The CDC recommends 20% or higher to reduce tick bites. :stopwatch:10% Picaridin will provide 5 hours of protection against mosquitoes and up to 7 hours for ticks. 20% protects for up to 7 hours against mosquitos and up to 8 hours against ticks.

DEET and Picaridin are chemical compounds, while Oil of Lemon Eucalyptus is an all-natural product. All-natural does not mean safer. Oil of Lemon Eucalyptus should not be used on those less than 3 years of age. DEET in concentrations up to 30%, can be used on kids 2 months and older. ALWAYS double-check the label to make sure the insect repellent you\xe2\x80\x99re selecting is appropriate for use in children. :check_mark:Some tips for safe use: :light_bulb:A higher percentage of repellent means longer lasting NOT stronger :warning_selector:Don\xe2\x80\x99t apply to cuts or wounds :nauseated_face:Don\xe2\x80\x99t apply to eyes or mouth. :waving_hand_light_skin_tone:Don\xe2\x80\x99t spray on the face! Spray on hands, then apply to face. :soap:Wash skin with soap and water when back indoors.

Source: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC)'

b'For a festive snack at home, try making this light and healthy black bean and corn salsa recipe from @tsp_basil with your family. It\xe2\x80\x99s easy to make with just a few simple fresh & pantry ingredients like Wild Harvest organic black beans and Big Win olive oil. Get the recipe below, and send us a pic of your tasty salsa! 
Ingredients:
1 (15 ounces) can (or 1 3/4 cup) black beans, rinsed and drained
1 (15 ounce) can corn, rinsed and drained
1 cup diced plum tomatoes
1 cup diced avocado
1/2 cup chopped scallions
1/2 cup fresh cilantro, chopped
dressing
2 tablespoons olive oil
1 large clove garlic, minced
1 teaspoon ground cumin
3 tablespoons fresh lime juice
1/4 teaspoon of salt 
Prepare:
1. In a medium bowl, toss together black beans, corn, tomatoes, avocado, scallions and cilantro.
2. In a separate bowl, whisk together olive oil, garlic, cumin, lime juice and salt.
3. Drizzle dressing over salad, then toss again.
4. Serve with tortilla chips or as a side for chicken, shrimp or fish.'

b'Time at home offers more time with family, like baking #Easter treats together. @mmschocolate eggs top soft, chewy cookies to make these "nests" irresistible! Get the recipe below:

Prep Time: 10 minutes
Cook Time: 15 minutes 
Total Time: 25 minutes (+ 30 minutes standing time)
Makes: 12 servings 
Ingredients: 
1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour
1/2 tsp baking powder
1/4 tsp salt
1/3 cup unsalted butter, at room temperature
3/4 cup granulated sugar
1 egg 
1 tsp vanilla extract
1 tbsp milk
1/3 cup confetti sprinkles 
36 M&M\xe2\x80\x99s Milk Chocolate Speckled Eggs 
Instructions: 
1.	Whisk together flour, baking powder and salt. Using electric mixer, beat butter with sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in egg; beat in vanilla. 
2.	Mix in flour mixture, alternating with milk, until fully incorporated. Refrigerate dough for at least 30 minutes. 
3.	Preheat oven to 350F. Divide dough into 12 portions; roll each portion into ball. Place sprinkles in small bowl; roll each dough ball in sprinkles. Place on parchment paper\xe2\x80\x93lined baking sheet. Do not flatten.
4.	Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly golden at edges. Press 3 M&M\xe2\x80\x99s Milk Chocolate Speckled Eggs into each cookie while still warm. Let cool completely on rack. 
Tip: Substitute pastel-colored decorating sugar for confetti sprinkles if desired.

Nutrition Facts 
Per 1 cookie
Calories 240
Fat 9g
Saturated Fat 4.5g
Cholesterol 30mg
Sodium 75mg
Carbohydrate 36g
Fiber 1g
Sugars 22g
Protein 3g'
